  "texts": [
    "As a reminder, the reference state in the central average scheme consists of fully occupied (unoccupied) remote valence (conduction) bands.",
    "The central bands are taken to have occupation 1/2 in the reference density matrix.",
    "If the Chern sector C has n C occupied bands, then its configuration can be described by a matrix spinor living in the Grassmannian projective space[74,257] SU (4) SU (n C) × SU (4n C) × U (1).",
    "(96) This could be the spin, valley, or layer degree of freedom.",
    "The flat metric condition requires that λ αβ (k, G) = ξ(G)δ αβ."
  ],
